  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Initiating Project Review**\n\nI\'m starting by inventorying the available files and assessing our skillset to determine relevance. The cloudsql abilities (execute, setup, and update) are being scrutinized for their potential contributions to **Polla Mundialista FOE**. I\'m focusing on how they align with the project\'s requirements.\n\n\n**Analyzing Persistence Strategies**\n\nI\'m now investigating the persistence needs for this prototype. I\'m carefully considering whether local storage, using React\'s context and `localStorage`, might suffice given the client-side prototype scope, or if a more robust solution, like Firebase, is truly necessary. The \"Backend\" specification suggests Firebase, but \"Storage & Persistence\" provides nuanced guidance on when and how to implement it. I\'ll need to check if the user specifically requests Firebase integration before proceeding.\n\n\n**Evaluating Single-View Scope**\n\nI\'m now determining if this project qualifies as a \"simple request\" to satisfy the single-view constraint, and if so, how to best handle the multiple screens described. My current assessment is that the complexity of the requirements and specifications, including the multiple screen mentions and Firestore schema, likely disqualify it as a \"simple\" request, and thus a single-view app.\n\n\n**Simulating Firebase Features**\n\nI\'m now contemplating a local simulation instead of full Firebase integration for the prototype. The \"Sandbox\" environment opens the door for a fully interactive simulation of all Firebase features, including Google Login, WhatsApp input, group code entry, and live updates, all with local storage for state persistence. I\'m focusing on whether a high-fidelity local simulation using Tailwind, styled perfectly with visual designs from the images, can meet the project\'s needs. I\'m also conducting a skills check to confirm the applicability of my abilities, and to verify what needs to be implemented. I\'m really keen on the client-side React App, especially with the shadcn-ui integration.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I am going to inspect the `package.json` file to understand the current structure and scripts."
