    thinking: "**Analyzing Visual Design**\n\nOkay, I\'m now delving into the visual design aspects of this web application. The initial focus is on the splash screen and login page, specifically the \"Acceso\" section. My notes highlight the background color, which is a dark `#121316`, alongside instructions to incorporate a dark blue stadium mesh and radial grid light patterns for the visual texture.\n\n\n**Designing the Entry**\n\nI\'m now sketching out the entry components. I envision a prominent, glowing soccer ball logo inside a neon-bordered circular badge, topped with bold text using Bebas Neue and a mono font for the subtitle. I\'ve designed a glass panel input for access code, Google login option, and \"Contact Admin\" link. Decorative elements include player counts and prizes in bright neon green. The initial modal will request a WhatsApp number. The design for the App Header, including the mini profile photo, title, points capsule, and phase pill, is also taking shape.\n\n\n**Developing the Match View**\n\nI\'m now iterating on the \"Inicio\" tab, focusing on the match list. I\'m finalizing the date dividers with elegant separators. For locked matches, I\'m designing grayscale cards with prediction results and award pills, and I\'ve designed interactive cards with score inputs for active matches, including the save button. A floating leaderboard action button is in the works. My work on the \"Reglas\" tab has started, with rules on scoring is being developed, specifically around accurate score and winner predictions.\n\n\n**Defining Tournament Stages**\n\nI\'m now outlining the tournament phases, specifically the \"Fases del Torneo\" card, which will detail the Groups and Knockouts stages. I\'m focusing on the special bonuses for Phase 2: Champion, Top Scorer, Clean Sheet, and Fair Play. Also, I\'m designing a large stadium graphic to set a spectacular background, with the inspirational text \"LA GLORIA TE ESPERA - Sigue las reglas, alcanza la cima\". I\'m also planning the \"Perfil\" tab.\n\n\n**Simulating Data Updates**\n\nI\'m now integrating mock data to simulate real-time updates. I\'m focusing on a \"Simulate Match Results\" function to update scores and rankings dynamically. My plan is to use simulated days, like \"Day 1,\" to trigger notifications, like \"\302\241Gol de M\303\251xico!\" and update user scores with exact, winner, and failed prediction scenarios, visualizing changes in real-time. This provides an interactive preview of application performance.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I am going to edit `index.html` to import the custom fonts and style icons used in the mockups. This ensures the design matches the requested screenshots."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 8
      nanos: 676047656
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
