  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Initial Data Structure**\n\nOkay, I\'m defining a file `/src/data.ts` to manage seed data and the logic to manage that data. I\'m focusing on defining the initial matches. I have a match of Alemania vs. Francia on \"JUE 11-06\" at \"09:00 AM\". I can use the flag links.\n\n\n**Acquiring Image Assets**\n\nI\'ve gathered high-quality image URLs for Alemania, Francia, and M\303\251xico. I\'m storing the URLs as strings. I\'m prioritizing accuracy and efficient asset retrieval.\n\n\n**Incorporating Image URLs**\n\nI\'ve successfully integrated high-quality image URLs for Argentina, Brasil, and Suiza into the data structure. These URLs are now associated with their respective countries, ready for use in the application\'s display. I\'m focusing on ensuring these links are correctly implemented.\n\n\n**Adding New Image Data**\n\nI\'ve added image URLs for Espa\303\261a and Croacia, integrating these new assets into the data structure seamlessly. Also I reviewed user data within the system, looking at user scores and global ranking data, from the system. I also noticed that the scoring calculation rule, as described in the system, appears to be a factor that must be considered.\n\n\n**Evaluating Scoring Rules**\n\nI am now delving into the point calculation logic. I\'ve confirmed the point system: exact match earns 5 points, correct winner with at least one correct goal earns 3, correct winner alone gets 2, and a miss is 0. I\'m reviewing the scoring function in TypeScript.\n\n\n**Revising Point Calculation**\n\nI\'m now clarifying the point allocation logic further. Analyzing a past match (Argentina vs. Mexico), I\'m trying to figure out how 25 points were awarded with an exact prediction. I see the base rule is 5 PTS for an exact match, but there are possibilities of some multiplier for some users. I am looking into how to best represent this in the UI, potentially using a contextual multiplier.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I am going to create `/src/data.ts` to implement static tournament seed data, group user listings, and prediction calculation helper functions aligned with the scoring rules."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 12
      nanos: 740583902
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
